        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses enclosed figures on elevation of terraces in several Scottish glens as surveyed by William Kemp and David Stevenson. Comments on Robert Chambers’ view of the terraces. Mentions a letter on the terraces, originally written for publication, which he has asked Robert Jameson [editor of the <hi rend="italic">Edinburgh New Philos. J.</hi>] to destroy.</p> 
